text.tspan: Vi and Jinx, the main characters of the show, are granted the most lines total when
combining both The Monster You Created and Welcome to the Playground. Vi is acing it
with 164 lines, followed by Jinx with a 100. Silco and Vander run close third and fourth,
respectively, despite each having a noticeable presence on only one of the two episodes.
Meanwhile, poor Boy Saviour, aka Ekko, is given minimum lines despite being present in
both episodes and thus making it to this chart.
Young Vi had over 110 lines in just the first episode, 8 of which were from when she
interrupted other characters like Mylo. This is the most anyone talked during Welcome to
the Playground or the Monster You Created. She gets much less talkative in the last
episode, where she talks for only about half what she did in the first. Jinx, on the other
hand, gets over 170% increase in lines total in the finale from when she was that small
Pow-pow in Welcome to the Playground.
Silco comes third in most talkative character when combining his lines total from both
episodes (91). Coming right after his adoptive daughter, Jinx, and followed by Vander with
his 90 lines. Most of Silco's lines in this comparison come from the last episode, where he
gets 79 whole lines making him the most talkative of all characters present in said
episode. Similarly, 82 out of Vander's 90 lines come from the first episode, while the
remaining eight comes from when he appears in Vi's head after she got herself knocked
out fighting with Sevika. Vander's first episode lines total equal Vi's average from both
episodes.
